<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Context Debt Report — promptc</title>
  <style>{{ styles | safe }}</style>
</head>
<body>

  <div class="page">

    {# ============ HEADER (2 lines, no card) ============ #}
    <header class="page-header">
      <div class="page-header__row">
        <span class="page-header__brand">promptc</span>
        <span class="status status--{{ status.level }}">
          <span class="status__dot"></span>{{ status.label }}
        </span>
      </div>
      <div class="page-header__path" title="{{ scan.root }}">{{ scan.root }}</div>
    </header>

    {% if scan.cursor_sibling_files %}
    <div class="banner cursor-warning">
      Detected <code>.cursor/rules/</code>
      ({{ scan.cursor_sibling_files }} file{{ '' if scan.cursor_sibling_files == 1 else 's' }})
      — not yet scanned. Cursor support is tracked for v0.2.
    </div>
    {% endif %}

    {# ============ HERO (huge grade letter + headline + 1 summary line) ============ #}

    {% if hero_state == "insufficient" %}
    <section class="hero hero--insufficient">
      <div class="hero__letter hero__letter--muted">—</div>
      <div class="hero__headline">{{ status.headline }}</div>
      <p class="hero__summary">{{ hero_summary }}</p>
      {% if scan.total_files > 0 %}
      <p class="hero__hint">
        Need at least 3 SKILL.md files <strong>and</strong> 1,000 body tokens.
        Scanning <code>.claude/</code> only — if your prompts live in
        <code>.cursor/rules/</code>, support is tracked for v0.2.
      </p>
      {% else %}
      <p class="hero__hint">
        promptc looks for <code>SKILL.md</code> under
        <code>.claude/skills/</code>, plus <code>commands/</code> and
        <code>agents/</code> — if your prompts live in
        <code>.cursor/rules/</code>, support is tracked for v0.2.
      </p>
      {% endif %}
    </section>
    {% else %}
    <section class="hero hero--{{ grade.letter | lower }}">
      <div class="hero__letter">{{ grade.display }}</div>
      <div class="hero__headline">{{ status.headline }}</div>
      <p class="hero__summary">{{ hero_summary }}</p>
    </section>

    {# ============ 3-KPI STRIP (no cards, just columns) ============ #}
    {% if kpis %}
    <section class="kpis">
      {% for k in kpis %}
      <div class="kpi">
        <div class="kpi__label">{{ k.label }}</div>
        <div class="kpi__value">{{ k.value }}</div>
        <div class="kpi__detail">{{ k.detail }}</div>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </section>
    {% endif %}

    <p class="hero-disclaimer">
      Token counts via OpenAI's <code>cl100k_base</code> as a Claude
      tokenizer proxy. Grade thresholds are heuristics.
      <a href="#methodology">See how this is graded</a>.
    </p>

    {# ============ MAIN: 70/30 — bare tables on left, alert panel on right ============ #}

    <div class="main">

      <div class="main__left">
        {% if top_duplicates %}
        <section class="block">
          <header class="block__header">
            <h2 class="block__title">Top duplicates</h2>
            <a class="block__link" href="#dups-detail">All {{ dedup.total_groups }} →</a>
          </header>
          <table class="bare-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th class="num">#</th>
                <th>Canonical file</th>
                <th class="num">Tokens</th>
                <th class="num">Files</th>
                <th>Type</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {% for g in top_duplicates[:5] %}
              <tr>
                <td class="num dim">{{ g.rank }}</td>
                <td><code class="path">{{ g.canonical_file }}</code></td>
                <td class="num">{{ "{:,}".format(g.wasted_tokens) }}</td>
                <td class="num dim">{{ g.size }}</td>
                <td>
                  {% if g.is_language_variant %}
                  <span class="tag tag--neutral">variant</span>
                  {% elif g.kind == "exact" %}
                  <span class="tag tag--critical">exact</span>
                  {% else %}
                  <span class="tag tag--warn">near</span>
                  {% endif %}
                </td>
              </tr>
              {% endfor %}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </section>
        {% endif %}

        <section class="block">
          <header class="block__header">
            <h2 class="block__title">Top {{ top_files | length }} largest files</h2>
            <span class="block__hint">By total tokens</span>
          </header>
          {% if top_files %}
          <table class="bare-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th class="num">#</th>
                <th>File</th>
                <th>Role</th>
                <th class="num" title="Total tokens including frontmatter and body">Tokens</th>
                <th class="num bloat-col" title="Share of this file's body that promptc flagged as duplicated with content elsewhere">Bloat</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {% for f in top_files %}
              <tr>
                <td class="num dim">{{ f.rank }}</td>
                <td><code class="path">{{ f.path }}</code></td>
                <td><span class="role role--{{ f.role }}">{{ f.role }}</span></td>
                <td class="num">{{ "{:,}".format(f.total_tokens) }}</td>
                <td class="num bloat-col">
                  {% if f.duplicate_tokens %}
                  <div class="bloat">
                    <div class="bloat__bar">
                      <div class="bloat__fill"
                           style="width: {{ (f.duplicate_ratio * 100) | round(0, 'floor') | int }}%;"></div>
                    </div>
                    <span class="bloat__pct">{{ "{:.0f}%".format(f.duplicate_ratio * 100) }}</span>
                  </div>
                  {% else %}
                  <span class="dim">—</span>
                  {% endif %}
                </td>
              </tr>
              {% endfor %}
            </tbody>
          </table>
          {% else %}
          <p class="empty">No files scanned.</p>
          {% endif %}
        </section>
      </div>

      <aside class="main__right">
        {% if top_risks %}
        <section class="block">
          <h2 class="block__title">Risks</h2>
          <ul class="alerts">
            {% for r in top_risks %}
            <li class="alert alert--{{ r.severity }}">
              <div class="alert__label">{{ r.label }}</div>
              <code class="alert__target">{{ r.target }}</code>
              <div class="alert__detail">{{ r.detail }}</div>
            </li>
            {% endfor %}
          </ul>
        </section>
        {% endif %}

        {% if insights %}
        <section class="block">
          <h2 class="block__title">Insights</h2>
          <ul class="insights">
            {% for i in insights %}
            <li class="insight">
              <div class="insight__finding">
                <span class="insight__dot insight__dot--{{ i.level }}"></span>
                {{ i.finding }}
              </div>
              <div class="insight__action">→ {{ i.action }}</div>
            </li>
            {% endfor %}
          </ul>
        </section>
        {% endif %}
      </aside>
    </div>
    {% endif %} {# end of non-insufficient main #}

    {# ============ ACCORDION DETAILS ============ #}

    {% if exposure.skill_count and exposure.multiplier and not scan.is_insufficient %}
    <details class="accordion" id="exposure-detail">
      <summary class="accordion__summary">
        <span class="accordion__chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <span class="accordion__title">Skill Context Exposure</span>
        <span class="accordion__hint">
          {{ "{:,}".format(exposure.total_promised) }} →
          {{ "{:,}".format(exposure.total_worst_case) }} tok
          · {{ "{:.1f}×".format(exposure.multiplier) }}
        </span>
      </summary>
      <div class="accordion__body card exposure">
        <p class="block__hint" style="margin-top:0">
          Worst-case context cost if a SKILL.md body ends up in context
          instead of just its description.
        </p>

        <div class="exposure__cells">
          <div class="exposure__cell">
            <div class="exposure__cell-label">Promised load</div>
            <div class="exposure__cell-value">{{ "{:,}".format(exposure.total_promised) }}</div>
            <div class="exposure__cell-hint">description tokens</div>
          </div>
          <div class="exposure__cell exposure__cell--warn">
            <div class="exposure__cell-label">Worst-case load</div>
            <div class="exposure__cell-value">{{ "{:,}".format(exposure.total_worst_case) }}</div>
            <div class="exposure__cell-hint">SKILL.md body tokens</div>
          </div>
          <div class="exposure__cell exposure__cell--critical">
            <div class="exposure__cell-label">Exposure multiplier</div>
            <div class="exposure__cell-value">{{ "{:.1f}×".format(exposure.multiplier) }}</div>
            <div class="exposure__cell-hint">body ÷ description</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        {% set max_load = exposure.total_worst_case if exposure.total_worst_case else 1 %}
        <div class="exposure__bars">
          <div class="exposure__bar-row">
            <span class="exposure__bar-label">Promised</span>
            <div class="exposure__bar-track">
              <div class="exposure__bar-fill exposure__bar-fill--ok"
                   style="width: {{ (exposure.total_promised / max_load * 100) | round(2) }}%;"></div>
            </div>
            <span class="exposure__bar-num">{{ "{:,}".format(exposure.total_promised) }}</span>
          </div>
          <div class="exposure__bar-row">
            <span class="exposure__bar-label">Worst case</span>
            <div class="exposure__bar-track">
              <div class="exposure__bar-fill exposure__bar-fill--bad"
                   style="width: 100%;"></div>
            </div>
            <span class="exposure__bar-num">{{ "{:,}".format(exposure.total_worst_case) }}</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        {% if exposure.files %}
        <h3 class="section-subhead">Top skills by worst-case load</h3>
        <table class="bare-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Skill</th>
              <th class="num">Worst-case</th>
              <th class="num">Promised</th>
              <th class="num">Mult.</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {% for f in exposure.files[:5] %}
            <tr>
              <td><code class="path">{{ f.file_path }}</code></td>
              <td class="num">{{ "{:,}".format(f.worst_case_tokens) }}</td>
              <td class="num">{{ "{:,}".format(f.promised_tokens) }}</td>
              <td class="num">
                {% if f.multiplier %}
                <strong>{{ "{:.1f}×".format(f.multiplier) }}</strong>
                {% else %}
                <span class="dim">n/a</span>
                {% endif %}
              </td>
            </tr>
            {% endfor %}
          </tbody>
        </table>
        {% endif %}

        {% if exposure.skills_without_description %}
        <p class="callout callout--warn">
          <strong>{{ exposure.skills_without_description | length }} skill(s) have no description field.</strong>
          Their promised load is 0, so there is no startup metadata to match
          against; the full body is the only way to know what they do.
        </p>
        {% endif %}

        <div class="sources">
          <p>Claude Code's Skills documentation describes the loading
          model: skill descriptions load into context at session start so
          Claude knows what's available, while the full SKILL.md body
          loads only when the skill is invoked.</p>
          <ul class="sources__links">
            <li>Docs: <a href="{{ anthropic_docs_url }}" rel="noopener">{{ anthropic_docs_url }}</a></li>
            <li>Community report of body loading anyway:
              <a href="{{ community_issue_url }}" rel="noopener">{{ community_issue_url }}</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="sources__disclaimer">The multiplier above is the ceiling
          of your exposure if the full body ends up in context. This tool
          makes no claim about whether that happens in your setup; it
          measures the upper bound.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>
    {% endif %}

    {% if top_duplicates %}
    <details class="accordion" id="dups-detail">
      <summary class="accordion__summary">
        <span class="accordion__chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <span class="accordion__title">Duplicate rules — {{ dedup.total_groups }} group{{ '' if dedup.total_groups == 1 else 's' }}</span>
        <span class="accordion__hint">
          Top {{ top_duplicates | length }} shown
          · {{ "{:,}".format(dedup.total_wasted_tokens) }} duplicate tokens
          {% if dedup.language_variant_groups %}
          · {{ dedup.language_variant_groups | length }} excluded as variants
          {% endif %}
        </span>
      </summary>
      <div class="accordion__body card">
        <p class="block__hint" style="margin-top:0">
          The canonical chunk (longest version) is highlighted; the other
          chunks are what promptc would consider redundant.
          {% if dedup.language_variant_groups %}
          Groups tagged <em>language variant</em> are per-binding SDK /
          language documentation copies — surfaced for visibility, but
          excluded from the Grade.
          {% endif %}
        </p>

        <div class="dups">
          {% for group in top_duplicates %}
          <article class="dup">
            <header class="dup__header">
              <span class="dup__rank">#{{ group.rank }}</span>
              <span class="dup__kind dup__kind--{{ group.kind }}"
                    title="{% if group.kind == 'exact' %}All chunks normalize to the same string after stripping markdown.{% else %}At least 0.85 Jaccard similarity on word sets after normalization.{% endif %}">{{ group.kind }}</span>
              {% if group.is_language_variant %}
              <span class="dup__variant"
                    title="Cluster paths differ only in known language segments (e.g. /python/ vs /go/) — treated as legitimate per-binding documentation, not bloat. Excluded from the Grade.">language variant</span>
              {% endif %}
              <span class="dup__wasted">
                {% if group.is_language_variant %}
                {{ "{:,}".format(group.wasted_tokens) }} tokens of repeated content
                {% else %}
                {{ "{:,}".format(group.wasted_tokens) }} duplicate tokens
                {% endif %}
              </span>
              <span class="dup__count dim">{{ group.size }} chunks</span>
            </header>
            <div class="dup__chunks">
              {% for chunk in group.chunks %}
              <div class="dup__chunk{% if chunk.is_canonical %} dup__chunk--canonical{% endif %}">
                <div class="dup__chunk-meta">
                  <code class="dup__chunk-path">{{ chunk.file_path }}</code>
                  <span class="dim">chunk {{ chunk.chunk_index }} · {{ "{:,}".format(chunk.tokens) }} tokens</span>
                  {% if chunk.is_canonical %}
                  <span class="dup__badge">canonical</span>
                  {% endif %}
                </div>
                <p class="dup__chunk-preview">{{ chunk.preview }}</p>
              </div>
              {% endfor %}
            </div>
          </article>
          {% endfor %}
        </div>
      </div>
    </details>
    {% endif %}

    <details class="accordion" id="methodology">
      <summary class="accordion__summary">
        <span class="accordion__chev" aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <span class="accordion__title">How this is graded</span>
        <span class="accordion__hint">Formulas · thresholds · caveats</span>
      </summary>
      <div class="accordion__body card methodology">
        <p class="block__hint" style="margin-top:0">
          promptc's grades and metrics are heuristics, not benchmarks. This
          section explains exactly how each number above was computed, so
          you can reproduce or contest any of them.
        </p>

        <h3 class="methodology__heading">Efficiency Grade</h3>
        <p>The grade reflects the <strong>duplicate-content ratio</strong>:
        the share of total scanned tokens that promptc flagged as a
        near-duplicate of content elsewhere in the scan. Includes duplicates
        from supporting docs (per-binding READMEs, references), not just
        SKILL.md bodies.</p>
        <pre class="methodology__formula">bloat_ratio = duplicate_tokens / total_tokens</pre>
        <table class="methodology__rubric">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Grade</th><th>Bloat ratio</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><span class="grade-pill grade-pill--a">A</span></td><td>&lt; 5%</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="grade-pill grade-pill--b">B</span></td><td>5% &mdash; 15%</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="grade-pill grade-pill--c">C</span></td><td>15% &mdash; 25%</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="grade-pill grade-pill--d">D</span></td><td>25% &mdash; 40%</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="grade-pill grade-pill--f">F</span></td><td>&ge; 40%</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
        <p>Each non-F letter splits into <code>+</code> (lower bloat half of the
        bracket) and <code>-</code> (upper half). F has no modifier.</p>
        <p class="methodology__caveat"><strong>These thresholds are heuristic.</strong>
        They were chosen by intuition before any reference distribution
        existed. v0.2 will replace them with empirical breakpoints derived from
        a corpus of real <code>.claude/</code> directories. Contributions
        welcome — see the project's roadmap.</p>

        <h3 class="methodology__heading">Skill Context Exposure</h3>
        <p>The exposure multiplier measures the ceiling cost if Claude loads
        a skill's full body instead of just its description at session start:</p>
        <pre class="methodology__formula">multiplier = SKILL.md body tokens / description tokens</pre>
        <p>Both numerator and denominator are <em>content tokens</em> —
        frontmatter overhead (delimiters, name, other fields) is excluded from
        both sides, so the ratio is symmetric.</p>
        <p>The behavior we're measuring is described in
        <a href="{{ anthropic_docs_url }}" rel="noopener">Claude Code's Skills
        documentation</a>: descriptions load at startup, full bodies on demand.
        Community reports describe setups where the full body ends up in
        context anyway — see
        <a href="{{ community_issue_url }}" rel="noopener">claude-code#14882</a>.
        promptc makes no claim about whether that happens in your setup; it
        measures the upper bound.</p>

        <h3 class="methodology__heading">Insufficient data</h3>
        <p>The "Not enough to audit yet" hero appears when:</p>
        <ul class="methodology__list">
          <li>fewer than 3 SKILL.md files <strong>OR</strong></li>
          <li>fewer than 1,000 aggregate body tokens across skills</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="methodology__caveat">These thresholds are heuristic too.
        They exist so a single tiny skill, or a few placeholder skills, doesn't
        get a misleading A+. They are not empirically calibrated.</p>

        <h3 class="methodology__heading">Token counts</h3>
        <p>{{ disclaimer }}</p>
        <p class="methodology__caveat">The ~18% bias is measured on
        English mixed prose/code (the anthropics/skills sample). Error
        magnitude on CJK content is unmeasured and may diverge further.
        Run <code>scripts/validate_tokenizer.py</code> against your own
        corpus (Anthropic native or OpenRouter) to calibrate for your
        content type.</p>
      </div>
    </details>

    <footer class="footer">
      <div>Generated by <strong>promptc</strong> v{{ version }}</div>
      <div class="footer__path">{{ scan.root }}</div>
    </footer>

  </div>

  <script>
    // Auto-open <details> when the URL hash points to it (zero-dep).
    function openTargetDetails() {
      try {
        var hash = location.hash;
        if (!hash || hash.length < 2) return;
        var el = document.querySelector(hash);
        if (el && el.tagName === 'DETAILS') el.open = true;
      } catch (e) { /* invalid selector — ignore */ }
    }
    window.addEventListener('hashchange', openTargetDetails);
    window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', openTargetDetails);
  </script>

</body>
</html>
